# Package version lockstep

Publishable packages **always share one version**:

- `packages/loom` → `@nodeweaver/loom`
- `packages/nodeweaver` → `nodeweaver`
- `packages/create-nodeweaver` → `create-nodeweaver`

## Rules

1. **Never bump one alone.** If any of the three changes version, update all three to the same number in the same commit (or same PR).
2. **Ship-ready bumps.** Any meaningful change that will go out in the next npm release must include a version bump before that release (patch for fixes/docs/CI publish plumbing; minor/major for features/breaks as usual).
3. **Keep helpers aligned.** Update version fallbacks that assume the shared version (e.g. `publishedLoomSpecifier` in `packages/nodeweaver/src/generators/loom-dependency.ts`).
4. **Do not bump** `@repo/shared` or other private workspace packages under this policy.

## Example

```text
# ❌ BAD — only scaffolder bumped
packages/nodeweaver/package.json → 0.1.3

# ✅ GOOD — lockstep
packages/loom/package.json              → 0.1.3
packages/nodeweaver/package.json        → 0.1.3
packages/create-nodeweaver/package.json → 0.1.3
```
